Add Windows color console sink to spdlog
- Introduced `wincolor_sink` and its associated header and implementation files to support colored logging in Windows console applications. - Implemented `wincolor_stdout_sink` and `wincolor_stderr_sink` for standard output and error streams. - Enhanced the spdlog library to include the new sinks and updated the necessary headers. - Added stopwatch functionality for measuring elapsed time in logging. - Updated logging mechanism in `HesLogPrivate` to handle message logging with timestamps and context information. - Implemented file logging capabilities with options for log file naming and path configuration.
